# Docker build context excludes — shared by infrastructure/Dockerfile.api and
# infrastructure/Dockerfile.nginx (both use dockerContext: .).
#
# Critical: never ship the host's node_modules into the context. pnpm populates
# node_modules with symlinks, which BuildKit cannot copy over the real packages
# that the image's own `pnpm install` (deps stage) produces — it fails with
# "cannot copy to non-directory". Each image installs its own deps from the
# lockfile, so host node_modules is never needed. This also drastically shrinks
# the upload context and speeds up Render's builds.

# Dependencies (every workspace) — reinstalled in-image from pnpm-lock.yaml
**/node_modules

# Build outputs — regenerated by `pnpm build` / `vite build` in-image
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# VCS / CI / editor
.git
.gitignore
.github
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# Local env & secrets — must never enter an image layer
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Test / coverage / logs
**/coverage
**/*.log
**/.vitest
**/test-results
**/playwright-report

# Docker build descriptors themselves (not needed inside the image)
**/Dockerfile*
**/docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore
